304
00:22:44,072 --> 00:22:44,656
You.

305
00:22:51,329 --> 00:22:52,789
Do you agree?

306
00:22:55,333 --> 00:22:56,710
Many will perish.

307
00:22:58,128 --> 00:23:01,256
Your confidence leaves me
with a strong impression.

308
00:23:02,757 --> 00:23:04,926
It's a curious thing for a simple ship guard...

309
00:23:05,176 --> 00:23:07,929
...to not lower his eyes
when questioned by me.

310
00:23:09,055 --> 00:23:11,808
That could've been just a lack of discipline.

311
00:23:13,018 --> 00:23:15,478
But a man's hands do not lie.

312
00:23:15,729 --> 00:23:16,813
They can reveal...

313
00:23:17,063 --> 00:23:21,067
...every imperfection
and flaw in his character.

314
00:23:22,027 --> 00:23:23,987
You see, your hands
are not rough enough...

315
00:23:24,237 --> 00:23:26,281
...to work the rigging of this ship.

316
00:23:27,824 --> 00:23:30,577
I know every single man beneath my lash.

317
00:23:30,827 --> 00:23:34,623
Can you explain to me
how I don't know you?

318
00:23:36,458 --> 00:23:38,668
Forgive me, commander.

319
00:23:41,379 --> 00:23:43,381
Let me introduce myself.

320
00:23:45,050 --> 00:23:45,759
Seize the spy.

321
00:23:46,009 --> 00:23:47,302
[GRUNTING]

322
00:23:49,888 --> 00:23:50,597
[YELLS]

323
00:24:05,236 --> 00:24:07,030
Coward.

324
00:24:08,198 --> 00:24:09,950
Storm is upon us.

325
00:24:12,786 --> 00:24:15,664
It's just some mad Greek weather.

326
00:24:27,175 --> 00:24:27,968
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

327
00:24:28,218 --> 00:24:30,470
SCYLLIAS: Themistokles.
- Come.

328
00:24:34,015 --> 00:24:35,308
Calisto.

329
00:24:35,558 --> 00:24:38,144
What is spoken here must not be repeated.

330
00:24:38,603 --> 00:24:39,813
Anywhere.

331
00:24:42,732 --> 00:24:45,944
My son has not earned the right
to sit at the table of combat veterans.

332
00:24:46,194 --> 00:24:48,571
- But you can trust him.
THEMISTOKLES: Very well.

333
00:24:50,490 --> 00:24:52,325
- Tell me.
- A Greek woman...

334
00:24:52,575 --> 00:24:54,869
...commands all of Xerxes' ships
to the south.

335
00:24:56,287 --> 00:24:57,914
Artemisia.

336
00:24:58,915 --> 00:24:59,916
I know of her.

337
00:25:00,959 --> 00:25:03,878
Artemisia is murderous by trade
with true skill on the sea...

338
00:25:04,129 --> 00:25:05,922
...and she has thirst for vengeance.

339
00:25:06,548 --> 00:25:08,049
Rumors are her entire family...

340
00:25:08,299 --> 00:25:10,593
...was murdered
by a squad of Greek hoplites.

341
00:25:11,678 --> 00:25:14,139
I have heard all the stories.

342
00:25:15,223 --> 00:25:17,851
And the hoplites spared no one on that day.

343
00:25:19,269 --> 00:25:21,271
[WOMAN SCREAMING]

344
00:25:44,335 --> 00:25:46,379
THEMISTOKLES: <i>The story goes
that they raped and murdered...</i>

345
00:25:46,629 --> 00:25:48,089
<i>...her entire family.</i>

346
00:25:50,133 --> 00:25:53,053
<i>And then they turned their attention
towards her.</i>

347
00:26:15,909 --> 00:26:19,412
<i>After years of being kept in the bowels
of a Greek slave ship...</i>

348
00:26:20,580 --> 00:26:23,124
<i>...she was discarded and left for dead...</i>

349
00:26:24,084 --> 00:26:26,669
<i>...where she was found near death
